{"nodes": [{"id": "math_theory_04_main", "label": "Theory Background 4 \u2014 Stochastic approximation and two-timescale theory (tool chain underpinning Layer S Theorem 4)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "title / \u00a70", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_robbins_monro_1951", "label": "Robbins-Monro 1951 stochastic approximation: \u03b8_{n+1} = \u03b8_n \u2212 a_n Y(\u03b8_n) converges to h(\u03b8)=0 under \u03a3 a_n=\u221e, \u03a3 a_n\u00b2<\u221e", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a71", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_kushner_yin_ode_method", "label": "Kushner-Yin ODE method (Ljung 1977, Kushner-Clark 1978): interpolated SA iterate converges to the ODE d\u03b8/dt=h(\u03b8); Lyapunov V\u2193 gives a.s. convergence (Thm 5.2.1)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a72", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_borkar_two_timescale", "label": "Borkar (2008) two-timescale SA: if b_n/a_n \u2192 0, the slow variable sees the fast one as quasi-stationary; dw/dt = g(\u03b8*(w), w) (Thm 6.1)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a73", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_martingale_convergence_application", "label": "Martingale convergence applied to SA: M_n = \u03a3 a_k \u03be_k has Var(M_n) \u2264 \u03a3 a_k\u00b2 M < \u221e \u21d2 M_n converges a.s.; noise term vanishes asymptotically", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a74", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_khasminskii_lyapunov", "label": "Khasminskii stochastic Lyapunov theorem: \u2112V = \u2207V\u00b7\u03bc + \u00bd Tr(\u03c3\u00b2 H_V) \u2264 \u2212c V \u21d2 X(t) \u2192 X* a.s. (LaSalle deterministic analogue)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a75", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_nes_score_function", "label": "NES / REINFORCE score-function identity: \u2207_\u03b8 E[f] = E[f \u00b7 \u2207_\u03b8 log p(x;\u03b8)]; for p=\ud835\udca9(\u03b8, \u03c3\u00b2I), \u2207log p = (x\u2212\u03b8)/\u03c3\u00b2 \u2014 forward-only gradient estimate", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a76", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_fisher_natural_gradient", "label": "Natural gradient / Fisher perspective of NES: EGGROLL rank-r specialization \u2207_W E[f(W+\u03b4W)] = E[f \u00b7 \u03b4W]/\u03c3\u00b2 with 1/r variance reduction (Theorem 5 rank-bias)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a76 (EGGROLL specialization)", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author": "ws", "contributor": "ws"}, {"id": "math_theory_04_connectivity_chain", "label": "Connectivity chain: Robbins-Monro \u2192 Kushner-Yin ODE \u2192 Borkar two-timescale \u2192 Martingale+It\u00f4 Lyapunov \u2192 EGGROLL Theorem 4, with REINFORCE\u2192NES\u2192EGGROLL parallel branch", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "raw/math_theory_04_stochastic_approximation.md", "source_location": "\u00a7\uc5f0\uacb0\uc131 \uc694\uc57d", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2026-04-24", "author